When writing CSS—as one does—I constantly and unintentionally trigger the inspector just by creating a new rule and hitting enter. Take this snippet, hit enter after `margin-bottom: 0;` and before the `}` and you'll see it.

```
.your-mom {
margin-bottom: 0;}
```

@mojombo was talking about URLs at summit, which made me think about the atom session URLs. 

And I was thinking about what to do when I come across a url pasted in chat way after the pairing session ended. 

So the pitch, wouldn't it be great that if the session is over, the app redirects the person to a compare page on .com showing the changes from the pairing session?

@github/atom
